# Engineering standards — [[HALF:PROJECT_NAME]]

> Scaffolded by `half` at tier **intermediate**. These are deterministic gates,
> not advisory docs. CI enforces them; `half standards check` reproduces the
> gate locally. Do not merge red.

The guiding principle (from both Anthropic's agent guidance and OWASP/SOC2):
**make correctness a runnable gate, not a paragraph someone might read.**

## Four pillars

### Quality
- Lockfile committed; dependencies pinned.
- Pre-commit runs format + lint + secret scan (`.pre-commit-config.yaml`).
- Conventional Commits enforced (`commitlint.config.cjs`).
- Linter + formatter + type-check wired into CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`).

### QA
- Test suite required and run in CI on every PR.
- Coverage tracked; threshold gate is project-owned (raise it over time).
- Changes land in a non-prod environment before production.
- Incremental scans on commit, full scans on build.

### Architecture
- Required review + branch protection, no bypass (`.github/BRANCH_PROTECTION.md`).
- Changes traceable to a ticket; author ≠ approver.
- Threat model kept current (`docs/THREAT_MODEL.md`).
- OWASP ASVS Level 2 baseline (`docs/ASVS-L2.md`).
- Centralized structured audit logging; RBAC + least privilege + MFA.

### Security
- Secret scanning (pre-commit + CI); secrets in env/vault, never in git.
- SCA dependency scan — blocking gate on HIGH/CRITICAL.
- SAST (semgrep + language-native) in CI.
- Deploy-blocking security gate (`audit.sh` mirrors CI).
- Signed commits; SBOM generated per build; container image scanned (trivy).
- Manual approval gate before production deploys.

## Agent-loop rules
Baked into `CLAUDE.md`. When an AI agent works this repo:
- One atomic task at a time; `/clear` context between unrelated tasks.
- Explore → Plan → Implement → Commit. Plan before multi-file work.
- Adversarial review in a fresh context (reviewer sees only the diff).
- Require evidence — test output, command result, screenshot — not "done".
- Things that must happen every time are hooks/CI gates, not prose.

